Bring a #saucepan{} of water up to the boil with @salt{0.5%tsp} for the pasta.

Add the @spaghetti{200%g} and simmer until tender, ~{8%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}, pop back in the pan, drizzle with @oil{1%tbsp} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1}(halved, peeled and chopped) into small pieces.

Halve the @yellow pepper{1}(halved, core and seeds discarded) and discard the core and seeds.

Chop into 1cm sized chunks.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{1%tbsp} in a #frying pan{} on medium high heat.

Fry the @Linda McCartney vegetarian meatballs{8} until starting to brown, ~{5-6%minutes}, turning frequently.

Remove from the pan to a #plate{}.

Pop your pan back on medium high heat, add a drizzle of @oil{1%tbsp} and the shallot and fry until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the pepper and fry for a further ~{2-3%minutes} stirring often.

Add the garlic, @tomato puree{30%g} and @dried Italian herbs{1%tsp} to the veg and stir through for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @tomatoes with basil{1%tin}(finely chopped), @vegetable stock powder{1} and @water{100%ml}.

Mix together, bring to a boil, then lower the heat and pop the veggie meatballs back in.

Simmer until the veggie meatballs are piping hot and the sauce has thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Once the sauce is cooked, taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if you feel it needs it.

Once everything is cooked, add the pasta to the pan with the sauce along with half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}.

Gently mix to combine.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if needed.

Divide the pasta equally between #plates{}.

Sprinkle with the remaining hard Italian cheese and enjoy!